11/08/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Two Serbian generals, former Army Chief of Staff Nebojsa Pavkovic and ex-Third Army Commander Vladimir Lazarevic, may soon surrender to the UN war crimes tribunal, Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Prvoslav Davinic said in an interview published Tuesday (10 August).There is also renewed speculation in Belgrade that Ratko Mladic would be handed over to the tribunal soon. 
Serbian authorities have denied repeatedly that they are negotiating with the fugitive Bosnian Serb general. 
(Reuters, AFP - 10/08/04)
